%erg v1
Title: Per-project beat config file (.claude/beat.json)
Created: 2026-04-30
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-30T09:15Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

`beat.py` currently reads all project config (budget overrides, etc.) from a
single harness-level `scripts/projects.json`. This couples project-specific
settings to the harness repo and makes it awkward to give one project a
different beat cadence.

Motivating use case: chemin-de-voix needs a 30-minute all-day beat (vs the
default nightbeat cadence) because its tickets are budget-constrained and
benefit from more frequent short runs.

## Design

Each project may have a `.claude/beat.json` file. `beat.py` reads it after
loading the `projects.json` entry and overlays any fields present.

**Schema (all fields optional):**
```json
{
  "budget_housekeeping": 0.40,
  "budget_pick_ticket": 0.50,
  "budget_raid": 10.00,
  "interval_minutes": 30
}
```

`projects.json` becomes a pure path list:
```json
[
  { "path": "~/aedist-technical-report" },
  { "path": "~/chemin-de-voix" },
  { "path": "~/git-erg" }
]
```

Existing per-project budget overrides in `projects.json` are migrated to each
project's `.claude/beat.json` and removed from `projects.json`.

**`interval_minutes` behaviour:** before running a project, `beat.py` checks
the project's `beat-log.jsonl` for the timestamp of the last completed run. If
`now - last_run < interval_minutes`, skip the project this tick. This lets a
30-min global timer serve projects with different cadences without extra
service/timer pairs.

## Actions

1. Add `interval_minutes` and budget fields to `ProjectConfig` dataclass in
   `beat.py`. Default `interval_minutes` to 0 (always run).
2. In `load_projects()`, after reading `projects.json`, check for
   `<project>/.claude/beat.json` and merge fields.
3. In the main beat loop, add the interval skip check before housekeeping.
4. Migrate existing budget overrides from `projects.json` to each project's
   `.claude/beat.json`.
5. Add `~/chemin-de-voix/.claude/beat.json` with `"interval_minutes": 30` and
   the higher `budget_raid` needed for its tickets.
6. Update `scripts/projects.json` to path-only format.

## Test

- `BEAT_DRY_RUN=1 python3 beat.py` shows correct per-project budgets loaded
  from `.claude/beat.json`.
- With `interval_minutes: 30`, a second dry-run within 30 min skips the
  project; one after 30 min runs it.

## Exit criteria

- `projects.json` contains only `path` keys.
- Each active project has `.claude/beat.json` with its budget/interval config.
- chemin-de-voix runs every 30 min; aedist and git-erg run every 60 min (or
  their configured cadence) from a single 30-min timer.
- All existing beat tests pass.
